  "source_id": "urinary-incontinence",
  "name": "Urinary Incontinence - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying UI patients via Condition + MedicationRequest. Path C (anticholinergic without UI dx) reflects undiagnosed overactive bladder.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete urinary incontinence patient population for a women's health and geriatrics initiative. Some patients have a coded UI diagnosis. Others are on antimuscarinic medications (oxybutynin, tolterodine, solifenacin) for overactive bladder symptoms without a formal UI diagnosis. Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis and antimuscarinics — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all UI patients.",
    "broad": "Find all urinary incontinence patients — by diagnosis or by antimuscarinic medication prescriptions (oxybutynin, tolterodine, solifenacin). Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run two queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|165232002 — UI dx. (2) MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|32675,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|119565,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|322167 — antimuscarinics. Union the patient IDs."
  },
